  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Give to every man that asketh of thee",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Literally, “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "be giving ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "implying a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "habit",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", not an instant act. Here again we have a broad, general principle of unselfishness and liberality safely left to the common sense of mankind, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 15:7-9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "spirit",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of our Lord’s precept is now best fulfilled by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "not",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " giving to every man that asks, because in the altered circumstances of the age such indiscriminate almsgiving would only be a check to industry, and a premium on imposture, degradation, and vice. By ‘giving,’ our Lord meant ‘conferring a boon;’ but mere careless giving now, so far from conferring a boon, perpetuates a curse and inflicts an injury. The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "spirit",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of the precept is large-handed but ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "thoughtful",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " charity. Love must sometimes violate the letter as the only possible way of observing the spirit (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 15:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 20:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
